  "local_port": 36536,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why isn\u2019t Pok\u00e9mon GO working?",
  "response": "If Pok\u00e9mon GO isn\u2019t working, there could be several reasons why. Here are some common issues and troubleshooting steps:\n\n### 1. **Server Issues**\n   - Pok\u00e9mon GO\u2019s servers may be down or experiencing high traffic. Check the official Pok\u00e9mon GO Twitter account, Niantic\u2019s status page, or community forums to see if others are reporting similar issues.\n   - **Solution:** Wait for the servers to come back online.\n\n### 2. **App Glitches or Bugs**\n   - The app may have a bug or glitch causing it to crash or freeze.\n   - **Solution:**\n     - Restart the app.\n     - Update the app to the latest version from the App Store (iOS) or Google Play Store (Android).\n     - Clear the app\u2019s cache (Android) or reinstall the app.\n\n### 3. **Internet Connection Problems**\n   - Pok\u00e9mon GO requires a stable internet connection. If your Wi-Fi or mobile data is weak or unavailable, the app won\u2019t work.\n   - **Solution:**\n     - Check your internet connection.\n     - Switch between Wi-Fi and mobile data to see which works better.\n     - Ensure your device has a strong signal.\n\n### 4. **GPS Issues**\n   - Pok\u00e9mon GO relies on GPS to function. If your device\u2019s GPS is not working correctly, the app may not load or track your location.\n   - **Solution:**\n     - Ensure Location Services are enabled for Pok\u00e9mon GO in your device\u2019s settings.\n     - Restart your phone to reset GPS functionality.\n     - Go to an open area with a clear view of the sky to improve GPS accuracy.\n\n### 5. **Outdated Device or OS**\n   - Pok\u00e9mon GO may not function properly on older devices or outdated operating systems.\n   - **Solution:**\n     - Update your device\u2019s operating system (iOS or Android).\n     - Check if your device meets the minimum requirements for Pok\u00e9mon GO.\n\n### 6. **Account Issues**\n   - Your account may be temporarily suspended, banned, or experiencing login issues.\n   - **Solution:**\n     - Try logging out and back into your account.\n     - If you suspect a ban, contact Niantic support for clarification.\n\n### 7. **Maintenance or Updates**\n   - Niantic may be performing maintenance or rolling out updates, which can temporarily disable the app.\n   - **Solution:** Wait until the maintenance or update is complete.\n\n### 8. **Third-party Apps or Jailbroken/Rooted Devices**\n   - If you\u2019re using a jailbroken (iOS) or rooted (Android) device or third-party apps, Niantic may block access to Pok\u00e9mon GO.\n   - **Solution:** Uninstall third-party apps or revert your device to its original state.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, you can contact Niantic Support for further assistance. Provide them with details about your issue, including your device model, operating system, and any error messages you\u2019re seeing.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
